	<body>
		<category name="ThaCampin'Dutchpack">
			<category name="Description">
				<comment>By Aaron0000</comment>
				<comment>Replaces a large number of items in the game with ports and interpretations of ThaCampin'Dutchman's arsenal from Borderlands 1.</comment>
				<comment>Notes;</comment>
				<comment>Some items have options available to them, such as which item it replaces, or an alternate skin and such.</comment>
				<comment>One of the items in this mod (Thermogenesis) uses a hotfix. Be sure to merge this mod with your main patch file.</comment>
			</category>
			<category name="Individual Item Descriptions">
				<category name="Weapons">
					<category name="Bandit Weapons">
						<category name="Dolos">
							<comment>Significantly increased pellet count, almost non-existent bullet speed. Increased critical hit damage.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Dog by default, but can also replace the RokSalt or Sledge's Shotgun instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Equuleus">
							<comment>Functions like a Revolver from Borderlands 1. Consumes three ammo per shot, increased magazine size.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Gub.</comment>
							<comment>Note; Allows the Gub to spawn in elements other than corrosive. Non-corrosive Gubs will be deleted if the mod isn't run.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Hawk">
							<comment>No recoil. Increased accuracy.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces RokSalt by default, but can also replace the Dog or Sledge's Shotgun instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Ophiuchus">
							<comment>Spawn in non-elemental only. Fires an explosive bullet that produces a different element of explosion depending on the type of enemy it hits. Consumes two ammo per shot.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Madhous!</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Sickle">
							<comment>High fire rate. Fires in the shape of a sickle.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Jolly Roger.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Traitor">
							<comment>x4 projectile count, very high fire rate, reduced accuracy, massize magazine size. Shooting once will attempt to empty the entire magazine of ammo.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Tattler by default, but can also replace the Bone Shredder or Orc instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Vulcan Fury">
							<comment>Incredible fire rate and magazine size. Minimal accuracy, slow projectile speed.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces CHOPPER.</comment>
							<comment>Note; There are two versions of the Vulcan Fury, one for use with the Unofficial Community Patch (on by default), and for use without it.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Zodiac">
							<comment>x12 projectile count, reduced damage per projectile. Massive magazine size. Fires E-Tech projectiles that produce smaller projectiles during flight. Consumes two ammo per shot.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Badaboom by default, but can also replace the Roaster instead.</comment>
						</category>
					</category>
					<category name="Dahl Weapons">
						<category name="Altair">
							<comment>x3 projectiles, reduced damage per projectile.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Sloth.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Barracuda">
							<comment>Dual element - Shock Bullet, Explosive splash. Rounds twist in flight, as well as ricochet off surfaces. Increased fire rate. Shock only.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Veruc.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Komodo">
							<comment>Four-round burst-fire outside of scopes. Divides into multiple rounds on impact that ricochet multiple times. Increased elemental damage and chance. Corrosive only.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Dahlminator by default, but can also replace the Teapot or Hornet instead.</comment>
						</category>
					</category>
					<category name="Hyperion Weapons">
						<category name="Agonizer">
							<comment>Explodes on contact with an enemy, penetrates enemies.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Logan's Gun.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Hitman">
							<comment>Impeccable accuracy, high damage, low fire rate.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Morningstar by default, but can also replace the Fremington's Edge or Invader instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Steve">
							<comment>HEYO!</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Bane.</comment>
							<comment>Note; Enables the Bane to spawn without an element. Non-elemental Banes will be deleted if you don't run the mod.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Wildfire">
							<comment>Incendiary only. Increased elemental effects. Has a unique firing pattern.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Heartbreaker.</comment>
							<comment>Note; Enables Heartbreaker to spawn with sights. Sighted Heartbreakers will be deleted if you don't run the mod.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Vanquish">
							<comment>x2 projectiles. Reduced damage per projectile. Increased critical hit damage</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Bitch.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Black Death">
							<comment>Creates a veritable hell of bullets upon ricohetting off a surface.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Conference Call.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Fusillation">
							<comment>Consumes 6 ammo per shot. Increased critical hit damage, reduced fire rate. Fires a large swath of projectiles.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Yellow Jacket by default, but can also replace the Commerce instead.</comment>
							<comment>Note; Enables the Yellow Jacket/Commerce to spawn in all elements. Non-Shock Yellow Jackets/Commerces will be deleted if the mod is not run.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Oneshot">
							<comment>Extremely high damage, critical hit damage, and accuracy. Extrememly low fire rate and reload speed. Magazine size of 1. Consumes 5 ammo per shot. Only spawns with Hyperion parts.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Invader by default, but can also replace Fremington's Edge or the Morningstar instead.</comment>
						</category>
					</category>
					<category name="Jakobs Weapons">
						<category name="Cricket">
							<comment>High knockback.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Judge by default, but can also replace the Law, Rex, Maggie, or Unforgiven instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Headbanger">
							<comment>x2 projectiles.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Skullmasher by default, but can also replace the Trespasser or Hawkeye instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Quash">
							<comment>High stats across the board, especially high magazine size. No sight. Has a two-round burst-fire when aiming down scopes.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces the Buffalo by default, but can also replace the Elephant Gun instead.</comment>
							<comment>Note; There are two version of the Buffalo replacer. One for use with the Unofficial Community Patch (on by default), and the other for standard Buffalo.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Sawed-Off">
							<comment>High projectile count, increased damage. Minimal accuracy, magazine size of 2. Consumes 2 ammo per shot. Projectiles had a very short life span.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Striker by default, but can also replace Triquetra, Tidal Wave, or Hydra instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Triple">
							<comment>Burst-fires three shots in rapid succession.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Maggie by default, but can also replace Law, Rex, Judge, or Unforgiven instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Wiseguy">
							<comment>The answer to everything.</comment>
							<comment>Always spawns with no accessory and a Jakobs grip.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Tidal Wave by default, but can also replace Triquetra, Striker, or Hydra instead.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Boneduster">
							<comment>Magazine size is always four. Fires a large amount of invisible projectiles. High knockback and recoil. Zooming in and firing will fire an incendiary charge shot that consumes four ammo per shot. Always spawns with no sight.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Tidal Wave by default, but can also replace Triquetra, Hydra, or Striker instead.</comment>
							<comment>Note; To achieve the charge shot effect, it uses and modifies the Badaboom's firing mode, affecting any mods that use it. If you aren't using a mod that replaces the Badaboom, use the Badaboom fixes included in the Boneduster areas to make the Badaboom function normally.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Money Shot">
							<comment>Consumes 4 ammo per shot. Fires in the shape of a $ sign, produces money upon shooting a surface.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Triquetra by default, but can also replace Tidal Wave, Hydra, or Striker instead.</comment>
							<comment>Note; To achieve the money drop effect, the Landscaper's mines had to be modified. Either use a Landscaper weapon replacer, or disable the money drops.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Railgun">
							<comment>High damage and critical hit damage. Fires railgun lasers. Consumes 2 ammo per shot.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Godfinger.</comment>
							<comment>Note; There is an optional version of the skin with stronger glow in the Skins folder.</comment>
						</category>
					</category>
					<category name="Maliwan Weapons">
						<category name="Earthquake">
							<comment>Explosive only. Ricochets upon hitting a surface.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Chere-Amie.</comment>
							<comment>Note; Forces the Chere-Amie to spawn without an elemental part. Will remain as such even if the mod is not run. Does not affect existing Chere-Amies.</comment>

							<comment>Produces a large Nova upon striking a surface. Increased damage and melee damage, reduced fire rate. Knocks enemies around.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Volcano.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Salvation">
							<comment>Heals allies when shooting them. Produces transfusion orbs upon shooting enemies. Passively restores health and ammunition. Actual damage to enemies is splash only.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Wanderlust.</comment>
						</category>
						<category name="Thermogenesis">
							<comment>Consumes 5 ammo per shot. Fires a powerful, slow-moving laser that erupts 8 times upon striking a surface. Slow fire rate, massively increased burn damage and chance.</comment>
							<comment>Replaces Pyrophobia.</comment>
							<comment>Note; This weapon uses the Logan's Gun projectile to achieve the erupting effect. Either use a Logan's Gun weapon replacer when using this weapon, or avoid using the Logan's Gun.</comment>
						</category>

			<category name="Weapons">
				<category name="Bandit">
					<category name="Legendary">
						<category name="Dolos" MUT="true">
							<category name="Dog replacer (Default)">
								<category name="Name/Red Text">
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog GestaltModeSkeletalMeshName SG_Barrel_Torgue</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_Dog PartName Dolos</code>
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Name.Title.Title__Unique_Dog:AttributePresentationDefinition_8 NoConstraintText You just activated my trap card!</code>
								</category>
								<category name="Rarity">
									<code profiles="default">set GD_Weap_Shotgun.Barrel.SG_Barrel_Bandit_Dog rarity (BaseValueConstant=5.000000,BaseValueAttribute=None,InitializationDefinition=None,BaseValueScaleConstant=1.000000)</code>
